DUBAI: Expo 2020 Dubai is preparing a slate of world-class events including ceremonies and musical shows in a celebration of the UAE’s 50th National Day next week. Running from Dec. 1-4, the celebrations will allow visitors to explore authentic Emirati experiences through stories, performances and cross-cultural conversations across the site’s pavilions. The UAE has announced that the holidays for federal entities and ministries will start from next Wednesday until Friday. 
The UAE National Day is celebrated every year to commemorate Dec. 2, 1971 when it declared independence as a sovereign nation.